result.execSummary:
The defendant Austyn J. Timm was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Austyn J. Timm is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Austyn J. Timm was found guilty of Burglary-Building or Dwelling, a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Austyn J. Timm in court with attorney Ryan T. Frank.  Defendant Austyn J. Timm in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Atty Hendee states that the matter is resolved and states plea agreement to Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed.  Atty Frank agrees.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees and enters a No Contest plea.
  Court questions defendant regarding plea. Advises of Constitutional Rights and elements of the charge.  Court finds plea made knowingly, voluntarily & Intelligently.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charges.  Court accepts defendant's plea and finds defendant guilty of Ct. 1.  Ct. 2 to be dismissed.

Atty Hendee states that all parties are waiving the right to a PSI.  Atty Frank agrees.
Atty Hendee makes sentencing recommendations.     State has complied with victim notification requirements.
Atty Frank makes sentencing arguments and asks the court to follow the joint recommendation.
Defendant makes a statement to the court.

BY THE COURT:  Ct. 1:  Court orders 6 years in the Wisconsin State Prison System with 3 years Initial Confinement and 3 years Extended Supervision with conditions; concurrent to all sentences that the defendant is currently serving
Report forthwith
Court Costs = $268.00
DNA Sample has already been submitted
Comply with any and all counseling recommended by the Agent
Eligible for Challange Incarceration Program and Substance Abuse Program
  **Court advises defendant that they have been convicted of a Felony and advises rights of voting privileges and of owning a firearm.

Ct. 2 to be dismissed.

Defendant Austyn J Timm in court with attorney Ryan T. Frank.  Defendant Austyn J Timm in custody.  Chad A. Hendee appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
  Atty Hendee states that in speaking with Atty Frank; the defendant will be waiving the Prelim today.  Atty Frank agrees and has discussed the waiver with his client.  Court questions the defendant.  Defendant agrees with the waiver.  Court accepts the waiver of the Prelim.

  BY THE COURT:  Court finds probable cause that a felony was committed and this defendant committed it.  Case bound over for trial or further proceedings.

Atty Hendee files the information with the Court.  Atty Frank states that the Defendant received a copy of the information and waives its reading.
Atty Frank enters a Not Guilty plea.

BY THE COURT:  Not Guilty plea entered.
Set for Return for this afternoon.
bond continued.  Return date scheduled for March 18, 2015 at 01:15 pm.
